Sleep deprivations can cause
hallucinations, definitely.

803
00:42:40,024 --> 00:42:41,616
But if it occurs again,
you'll let me know?

804
00:42:41,659 --> 00:42:42,648
All right?

805
00:42:42,693 --> 00:42:43,717
- All right.

806
00:42:43,761 --> 00:42:45,729
- Why aren't you sleeping?
- Work.

807
00:42:45,763 --> 00:42:47,060
It's brutal right now.

808
00:42:47,097 --> 00:42:48,928
Tons of big cases.

809
00:42:48,966 --> 00:42:53,198
And on top of that,
Robin and I are separated.

810
00:42:53,237 --> 00:42:54,829
- Oh?

811
00:42:54,872 --> 00:42:56,601
- Yeah, I think with Robin and me,

812
00:42:56,640 --> 00:42:58,665
it's a game of marital chicken,
you know?

813
00:42:58,709 --> 00:43:00,506
Just give each other
a good scare and move on.

814
00:43:00,544 --> 00:43:01,670
I think we'll be all right.

815
00:43:01,712 --> 00:43:02,906
- Yes, I think it'll work out.

816
00:43:02,947 --> 00:43:03,936
You're a good couple.

817
00:43:03,981 --> 00:43:06,006
- But in the meantime,
I moved into my aunt's house.

818
00:43:06,050 --> 00:43:09,315
And I got to tell you,
I haven't been alone in...

819
00:43:09,353 --> 00:43:10,945
- I'm sorry.
You moved where?

820
00:43:10,988 --> 00:43:12,455
- To my aunt's house for now.

821
00:43:12,489 --> 00:43:14,081
- Oh.

822
00:43:14,124 --> 00:43:16,524
And is that where you had
this hallucination?

823
00:43:16,560 --> 00:43:17,584
- Yep.

824
00:43:17,628 --> 00:43:24,397
- And this ghostlike image,
was it male or female?

825
00:43:24,435 --> 00:43:26,699
- It was a woman.

826
00:43:26,737 --> 00:43:27,829
- Oh.

827
00:43:27,871 --> 00:43:31,466
Was there anything about this woman
that was interesting or odd?

828
00:43:31,508 --> 00:43:35,877
Anything about her face
or her eyes?

829
00:43:35,913 --> 00:43:38,347
- I couldn't say.

830
00:43:38,382 --> 00:43:39,849
I just saw it from the back.

831
00:43:39,883 --> 00:43:40,975
- It?

832
00:43:43,988 --> 00:43:45,785
- Her.

833
00:43:45,823 --> 00:43:47,313
Her.

834
00:43:47,358 --> 00:43:48,347
- [chuckles]

835
00:43:48,392 --> 00:43:49,381
Excuse me.

836
00:43:49,426 --> 00:43:51,223
I was just struck with the memory

837
00:43:51,261 --> 00:43:55,027
of the first time your father
brought you here.

838
00:43:55,065 --> 00:43:57,363
It was just after your mother passed.

839
00:43:57,401 --> 00:44:00,063
I was new to my profession,
unsure of myself.

840
00:44:00,104 --> 00:44:03,301
And you were this
precocious little guy

841
00:44:03,340 --> 00:44:05,069
who looked at my diploma wall
and asked

842
00:44:05,109 --> 00:44:07,304
why I hadn't been
to one of the top med schools.

843
00:44:07,344 --> 00:44:09,608
- Oh, Jesus.

844
00:44:09,647 --> 00:44:10,636
Did I?

845
00:44:10,681 --> 00:44:12,581
- Yeah, we did good work though.

846
00:44:12,616 --> 00:44:13,844
We were making progress.

847
00:44:13,884 --> 00:44:15,875
And then...

848
00:44:15,919 --> 00:44:19,514
well, I always thought your father
pulled you out too soon.

849
00:44:19,556 --> 00:44:20,818
- My dad hated shrinks.

850
00:44:20,858 --> 00:44:23,827
I think he feared that if you
poked around in my head,

851
00:44:23,861 --> 00:44:26,022
you might discover some
deep family secret.

852
00:44:26,063 --> 00:44:27,553
- Hmm.

853
00:44:27,598 --> 00:44:31,466
Well, whatever the reason,
I think you came out of it too soon.

854
00:44:31,502 --> 00:44:32,526
- Hence my insomnia.

855
00:44:32,569 --> 00:44:33,866
- And your issues with death.

856
00:44:33,904 --> 00:44:35,269
What I think you need...

857
00:44:35,305 --> 00:44:37,170
- Is to spend more time on your couch.

858
00:44:37,207 --> 00:44:38,196
Yeah, I know.

859
00:44:38,242 --> 00:44:39,903
You suggest that every year.

860
00:44:39,943 --> 00:44:41,433
- Well, what do you think of it this year?

861
00:44:41,478 --> 00:44:43,969
- I think you drive a fancy enough car.

862
00:44:44,014 --> 00:44:45,572
You don't need another patient.

863
00:44:46,817 --> 00:44:47,875
- Ooh.

864
00:44:47,918 --> 00:44:49,249
You're getting better.

865
00:44:49,286 --> 00:44:50,913
- Thanks, Doc.

866
00:44:50,954 --> 00:44:53,514
Appreciate it.

867
00:44:57,461 --> 00:44:58,450
It's funny though.

868
00:44:58,495 --> 00:45:00,861
You mentioned my mother.

869
00:45:00,898 --> 00:45:02,763
It's sad.

870
00:45:02,800 --> 00:45:05,735
I can barely remember her.

871
00:45:05,769 --> 00:45:11,036
Except for tidbits,

872
00:45:11,075 --> 00:45:12,235
there's nothing.

873
00:45:12,276 --> 00:45:13,834
- She's in there, Bryan.

874
00:45:13,877 --> 00:45:16,437
She's in there.

875
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:33,720
[birds cawing]

876
00:45:55,886 --> 00:45:58,081
[glass shatters]

877
00:45:58,122 --> 00:46:00,283
[loud shattering]

878
00:46:00,324 --> 00:46:04,158
[women screaming]

879
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:10,489
- Ver Staaten.

880
00:46:10,534 --> 00:46:11,694
Dr. Shepard.

881
00:46:11,735 --> 00:46:15,364
Okay, I'll be right there.

882
00:46:15,405 --> 00:46:16,394
Hi.

883
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:18,601
Hey, you.

884
00:46:18,642 --> 00:46:20,041
I can't do this right now.

885
00:46:20,077 --> 00:46:21,874
I have a meeting.

886
00:46:21,912 --> 00:46:23,277
This is for him.

887
00:46:23,313 --> 00:46:26,407
He thinks you left us
for another family.

888
00:46:26,450 --> 00:46:27,678
Oome on.

889
00:46:34,958 --> 00:46:35,947
- You a werewolf?

890
00:46:35,993 --> 00:46:37,460
Whoa.

891
00:46:37,494 --> 00:46:38,586
Scary werewolf.

892
00:46:38,629 --> 00:46:39,618
No.

893
00:46:39,663 --> 00:46:40,652
Not scary.

894
00:46:40,697 --> 00:46:41,891
- Oh, okay, not scary.

895
00:46:41,932 --> 00:46:43,399
There's nobody here but me, pal.

896
00:46:43,433 --> 00:46:45,799
Do you want to look for yourself?

897
00:46:45,836 --> 00:46:47,030
You want to explore?

898
00:46:47,070 --> 00:46:48,059
Okay.

899
00:46:48,105 --> 00:46:49,094
Hurry up.

900
00:46:49,139 --> 00:46:51,767
Dad's got a meeting.

901
00:46:56,713 --> 00:46:58,203
- What are you doing here?

902
00:46:58,248 --> 00:46:59,840
- We need some time apart, Robin.

903
00:46:59,883 --> 00:47:01,248
- I want us in therapy.

904
00:47:01,285 --> 00:47:02,445
- Therapy.

905
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:04,181
- Yeah.

906
00:47:04,221 --> 00:47:05,916
- I have my doubts about therapy.

907
00:47:05,956 --> 00:47:07,719
- Oh, you have your doubts
about everything.

908
00:47:07,758 --> 00:47:10,556
All you do all day is have doubts
about what everyone else thinks.

909
00:47:10,594 --> 00:47:11,856
- Well, uh, what would you rather, Robin,

910
00:47:11,895 --> 00:47:13,260
I was one a those fanatics
who was certain?

911
00:47:13,297 --> 00:47:16,391
- You are every bit as certain
as any fanatic I've ever seen.

912
00:47:16,433 --> 00:47:17,491
- Okay, that's absurd.

913
00:47:17,534 --> 00:47:19,525
That is an absurd thing to say.

914
00:47:19,570 --> 00:47:21,731
I am not certain about anything,
and if you can't see that,

915
00:47:21,772 --> 00:47:23,672
we're even farther apart
than I thought we were.

916
00:47:23,707 --> 00:47:24,833
- So what do you call it then

917
00:47:24,875 --> 00:47:26,775
when you are so positive
the rest of us are wrong,

918
00:47:26,810 --> 00:47:28,107
flawed in our thinking?

919
00:47:28,145 --> 00:47:30,136
I call that certain, arrogant.

920
00:47:30,180 --> 00:47:32,546
And I don't think it's 'cause
you're smarter than anyone else.

921
00:47:32,583 --> 00:47:33,777
I think it's 'cause you're lost.

922
00:47:33,817 --> 00:47:35,011
- Well, guess what, Robin.

923
00:47:35,052 --> 00:47:36,383
I hardly care what you think,

924
00:47:36,420 --> 00:47:38,615
'cause I got trial in the morning,
I lost my expert,

925
00:47:38,655 --> 00:47:40,088
and I got a 200 page deposition...

926
00:47:40,123 --> 00:47:42,387
- Is it your mother?

927
00:47:42,426 --> 00:47:44,018
- What?

928
00:47:44,061 --> 00:47:46,586
- I said, is it your mother?

929
00:47:46,630 --> 00:47:52,535
Is that why you're messed up,
'cause of what happened to her,

930
00:47:52,569 --> 00:47:55,265
'cause of what you saw that day?

931
00:47:55,305 --> 00:47:57,500
- My mother died when I was five.

932
00:47:57,541 --> 00:47:59,065
I barely remember her.

933
00:47:59,109 --> 00:48:00,303
- I don't believe it.

934
00:48:00,344 --> 00:48:01,572
- Oh, you think I'm lying?

935
00:48:01,612 --> 00:48:03,807
- I think that you've buried stuff.

936
00:48:03,847 --> 00:48:05,508
I think that you saw more
that day in Boston

937
00:48:05,549 --> 00:48:06,538
than they told you.

938
00:48:06,583 --> 00:48:08,244
- All right, you know what we're
not gonna do?

939
00:48:08,285 --> 00:48:11,118
We are not going to play
psychobabble with my head.

940
00:48:11,154 --> 00:48:12,143
- Listen...

941
00:48:12,189 --> 00:48:13,986
- My mother is not the problem
with our marriage.

942
00:48:14,024 --> 00:48:16,424
So for you to try to pin it on a woman
who's been dead for 38 years...

943
00:48:16,460 --> 00:48:18,928
- Do you know you
talk about her in your sleep?

944
00:48:18,962 --> 00:48:21,590
- I what?

945
00:48:21,632 --> 00:48:23,156
- And I've never told you before,

946
00:48:23,200 --> 00:48:25,065
because I thought it would
make things worse.

947
00:48:25,102 --> 00:48:27,263
When you talk about her,

948
00:48:27,304 --> 00:48:28,635
you talk about her face.

949
00:48:28,672 --> 00:48:30,162
All right, God damn it, that's enough.

950
00:48:30,207 --> 00:48:31,196
Let this alone!

951
00:48:31,241 --> 00:48:32,401
- This is the shit that is
ruining our marriage!

952
00:48:32,442 --> 00:48:34,842
- No, you're doing it,
because you won't stop.

953
00:48:34,878 --> 00:48:36,778
- You sit up in bed like a child

954
00:48:36,813 --> 00:48:38,974
terrified,
staring across the room.

955
00:48:39,016 --> 00:48:40,415
You know what you're looking at?

956
00:48:40,450 --> 00:48:41,439
You're looking at her!

957
00:48:41,485 --> 00:48:42,474
You see her!

958
00:48:42,519 --> 00:48:43,645
- Stop this!

959
00:48:43,687 --> 00:48:44,676
- [screams]

960
00:48:44,721 --> 00:48:45,710
- Mama!

961
00:48:45,756 --> 00:48:46,950
- Michael!

962
00:48:46,990 --> 00:48:48,082
- Michael?
- Where is he?

963
00:48:48,125 --> 00:48:49,353
- Michael!

964
00:48:49,393 --> 00:48:51,554
Michael!

965
00:48:58,268 --> 00:49:00,862
- Baby?

966
00:49:00,904 --> 00:49:05,500
- Someone's in the closet.

967
00:49:05,542 --> 00:49:06,531
- What?

968
00:49:07,878 --> 00:49:09,812
- They said my name.

969
00:49:09,846 --> 00:49:11,370
- Oh, no, sweetheart.

970
00:49:11,415 --> 00:49:12,712
There's nobody here but Daddy.

971
00:49:12,749 --> 00:49:14,273
- Maybe it's a ghost.

972
00:49:14,318 --> 00:49:15,376
- Oh, no, baby.

973
00:49:15,419 --> 00:49:18,547
Remember what Daddy and I
told you about ghosts?

974
00:49:18,588 --> 00:49:21,557
So what did Daddy and I
tell you about ghosts?

975
00:49:21,591 --> 00:49:22,580
Daddy?

976
00:49:22,626 --> 00:49:24,184
What did we tell Michael about ghosts?

977
00:49:25,862 --> 00:49:26,851
- They're not real.

978
00:49:26,897 --> 00:49:28,228
- They're not real.

979
00:49:28,265 --> 00:49:29,254
Okay?

980
00:49:29,299 --> 00:49:31,358
It's just your imagination again,
sweet pie.

981
00:49:31,401 --> 00:49:32,561
- Oome here, pal.

982
00:49:39,543 --> 00:49:42,410
They sure do seem real
sometimes though, don't they?

983
00:49:42,446 --> 00:49:45,643
[door creaks]

984
00:50:03,934 --> 00:50:05,162
- Hmm.

985
00:50:05,202 --> 00:50:06,692
Sully.

986
00:50:26,456 --> 00:50:29,448
[leaves rustling]

987
00:50:31,728 --> 00:50:33,628
Oh, come on.

988
00:50:54,618 --> 00:50:57,109
Oh, Jesus Ohrist!

989
00:50:59,089 --> 00:51:00,488
It's you.

990
00:51:00,524 --> 00:51:02,458
- So this is the big, bad, house, huh?

991
00:51:02,492 --> 00:51:04,460
I might be too nervous to come in.

992
00:51:04,494 --> 00:51:07,520
- Nobody asked you in.

993
00:51:09,533 --> 00:51:11,228
What, are you plannin'
on spending the night?

994
00:51:11,268 --> 00:51:12,257
- Uh-huh.

995
00:51:12,302 --> 00:51:13,769
I heard you saw something here.

996
00:51:13,804 --> 00:51:15,032
And I'm intrigued.

997
00:51:15,072 --> 00:51:16,801
- What I saw was not real.

998
00:51:17,941 --> 00:51:19,772
Excuse me.

999
00:51:19,810 --> 00:51:21,300
Excuse me.

1000
00:51:21,344 --> 00:51:23,107
You can't just walk in here.

1001
00:51:23,146 --> 00:51:24,443
Hey!

1002
00:51:24,481 --> 00:51:26,472
What do you think you're doing?

1003
00:51:26,516 --> 00:51:30,646
This is my house.

1004
00:51:30,687 --> 00:51:32,120
- There's something here.

1005
00:51:32,155 --> 00:51:33,554
- Okay.

1006
00:51:33,590 --> 00:51:34,579
What?

1007
00:51:34,624 --> 00:51:36,023
What do you think I saw?

1008
00:51:36,059 --> 00:51:37,356
- A ghost.

1009
00:51:37,394 --> 00:51:38,827
- I don't believe in ghosts.

1010
00:51:38,862 --> 00:51:40,989
- Well, that's ironic,
since you're the one that saw it.

1011
00:51:41,031 --> 00:51:43,864
- What I saw was a hallucination
caused by sleep deprivation.

1012
00:51:43,900 --> 00:51:44,889
- Yeah.

1013
00:51:44,935 --> 00:51:45,993
My shrink would say that too.

1014
00:51:46,036 --> 00:51:47,094
[chuckles]

1015
00:51:47,137 --> 00:51:50,163
Look, it's not as out there
as it seems, you know,

1016
00:51:50,207 --> 00:51:51,799
the whole ghost thing.

1017
00:51:51,842 --> 00:51:55,505
In fact, 46% of the people
in this country believe in ghosts.

1018
00:51:55,545 --> 00:51:58,844
46% of the people in this country
can't find Europe on a map.

1019
00:51:58,882 --> 00:52:00,144
- Oh, wow.

1020
00:52:00,183 --> 00:52:01,172
You know something?

1021
00:52:01,218 --> 00:52:04,187
You're very arrogant.

1022
00:52:04,221 --> 00:52:05,279
- I'm sorry.

1023
00:52:05,322 --> 00:52:06,311
- Don't be.

1024
00:52:06,356 --> 00:52:07,345
I like that.

1025
00:52:08,825 --> 00:52:09,985
- You still can't stay.

1026
00:52:10,026 --> 00:52:11,891
- You're a lawyer, right?

1027
00:52:11,928 --> 00:52:13,156
- Yes.

1028
00:52:13,196 --> 00:52:15,061
- That means you get off on logic, proof.

1029
00:52:15,098 --> 00:52:17,032
- I don't know if I get off on
them, but...

1030
00:52:17,067 --> 00:52:19,558
- Even Koven, the fool,
believes I'm psychic.

1031
00:52:19,603 --> 00:52:20,934
- I don't believe in ESP.

1032
00:52:20,971 --> 00:52:21,960
- No, no, no.

1033
00:52:22,005 --> 00:52:25,168
You're missing my point.

1034
00:52:25,208 --> 00:52:27,733
You saw something here.

1035
00:52:27,777 --> 00:52:34,580
So just suppose for a moment
you let me stay and I see something too.

1036
00:52:34,618 --> 00:52:36,552
And since you haven't described
what you saw

1037
00:52:36,586 --> 00:52:39,077
except as a woman at the bottom
of some stairs,

1038
00:52:39,122 --> 00:52:45,925
then if I see her too,
and I could describe her, well,

1039
00:52:45,962 --> 00:52:50,331
I mean, that would be proof
of something, wouldn't it?

1040
00:52:50,367 --> 00:52:52,267
Good proof.

1041
00:52:52,302 --> 00:52:53,929
- You can have this bedroom
right over here.

1042
00:52:53,970 --> 00:52:55,028
It's got its own bath.

1043
00:52:55,071 --> 00:52:57,733
I'll be up on the third floor
if you need s...

1044
00:53:00,443 --> 00:53:01,467
Oh, no.

1045
00:53:01,511 --> 00:53:03,479
No, no.
I'm sorry.

1046
00:53:03,513 --> 00:53:04,639
This was my aunt's room,

1047
00:53:04,748 --> 00:53:05,737
the one that died.

1048
00:53:05,782 --> 00:53:06,771
- Oh.

1049
00:53:06,816 --> 00:53:08,306
So it's vacant.

1050
00:53:08,351 --> 00:53:10,319
- Yeah.
Right.

1051
00:53:10,353 --> 00:53:13,151
Whatever.

1052
00:53:13,190 --> 00:53:14,350
Hey, let me ask you something.

1053
00:53:14,391 --> 00:53:16,757
How does a girl your age
get a brand-new Porsche?

1054
00:53:16,793 --> 00:53:17,782
- I come from money.

1055
00:53:17,827 --> 00:53:18,953
- And your folks?

1056
00:53:18,995 --> 00:53:20,895
- My mother ran away when I was six,

1057
00:53:20,931 --> 00:53:22,421
and my father passed away
this summer.

1058
00:53:22,465 --> 00:53:23,454
- Hmm.

1059
00:53:23,500 --> 00:53:24,933
I'm sorry then about your
father.

1060
00:53:24,968 --> 00:53:26,128
- No, don't be.

1061
00:53:26,169 --> 00:53:27,932
- What, you two weren't close?

1062
00:53:27,971 --> 00:53:31,407
- Not in a good way.

1063
00:53:33,610 --> 00:53:34,907
- Do you have siblings?

1064
00:53:34,945 --> 00:53:35,934
- Yeah, I have a brother.

1065
00:53:35,979 --> 00:53:38,447
He's in a mental institution.

1066
00:53:38,481 --> 00:53:40,244
He's been there since he was 13.

1067
00:53:40,283 --> 00:53:42,945
And you probably figured
