01:08:25,768 --> 01:08:31,866
- I hallucinated something
in the house.

1338
01:08:31,907 --> 01:08:34,808
I saw my mother.

1339
01:08:34,844 --> 01:08:38,371
Shepard assures me it's just
sleep deprivation.

1340
01:08:38,414 --> 01:08:40,439
- You've been sleep deprived before.

1341
01:08:40,483 --> 01:08:41,950
Ever see anything?

1342
01:08:41,984 --> 01:08:43,849
- No.

1343
01:08:43,886 --> 01:08:45,911
- Well, that's interesting,

1344
01:08:45,955 --> 01:08:48,651
because I remember
the first time you saw her.

1345
01:08:48,691 --> 01:08:50,386
- Pardon?

1346
01:08:50,426 --> 01:08:52,860
- Eight days after she was buried.

1347
01:08:52,895 --> 01:08:54,157
- Is that true?

1348
01:08:54,196 --> 01:08:56,289
- That time frightened you so badly

1349
01:08:56,332 --> 01:08:57,799
it led to a breakdown

1350
01:08:57,833 --> 01:09:00,301
and to them having to get you away
from the house permanently.

1351
01:09:00,336 --> 01:09:03,669
Your father sold it
to your aunt and uncle

1352
01:09:03,706 --> 01:09:05,901
and then bought the one up
in Farmbrook for the two of you.

1353
01:09:05,941 --> 01:09:07,067
- That's what happened.

1354
01:09:07,109 --> 01:09:10,704
- Of course,
everyone dismissed what you saw

1355
01:09:10,746 --> 01:09:12,646
until something happened to your uncle.

1356
01:09:12,681 --> 01:09:14,876
I don't know exactly what happened,

1357
01:09:14,917 --> 01:09:19,377
but he became thoroughly convinced
that there was a presence in the house.

1358
01:09:19,421 --> 01:09:21,855
- The shrine in the closet.

1359
01:09:21,891 --> 01:09:22,880
- That was his.

1360
01:09:22,925 --> 01:09:25,450
- Your aunt thought he was a fool.

1361
01:09:25,494 --> 01:09:27,121
She was a skeptic like you.

1362
01:09:27,163 --> 01:09:28,494
But interestingly enough,

1363
01:09:28,531 --> 01:09:30,396
she couldn't bring herself
to tear it down

1364
01:09:30,432 --> 01:09:31,763
even after he died.

1365
01:09:31,800 --> 01:09:34,769
And then, in the last year of her life,

1366
01:09:34,803 --> 01:09:38,933
she began to believe it herself,
said she felt it for the first time,

1367
01:09:38,974 --> 01:09:42,603
felt that it was angry at her
for not leaving the house to you.

1368
01:09:42,645 --> 01:09:44,203
- This has a history?

1369
01:09:44,246 --> 01:09:46,077
- This has a history.

1370
01:09:46,115 --> 01:09:47,878
- What else do you know?

1371
01:09:47,917 --> 01:09:50,249
In the church,
you warned me about the house.

1372
01:09:50,286 --> 01:09:51,719
You spoke of this evil presence.

1373
01:09:51,754 --> 01:09:52,743
- What did you mean?

1374
01:09:55,391 --> 01:10:00,488
- Have you ever wondered why you
can't remember your mother, Bryan?

1375
01:10:00,529 --> 01:10:02,963
- Because she died when I was five.

1376
01:10:02,998 --> 01:10:04,431
- Five-year-olds have memories,

1377
01:10:04,466 --> 01:10:07,697
unless they don't want to have memories,

1378
01:10:07,736 --> 01:10:09,169
unless they're bad memories,

1379
01:10:09,205 --> 01:10:11,730
unless they're memories
of being locked in a closet

1380
01:10:11,774 --> 01:10:14,538
when they were terrified of darkness,

1381
01:10:14,577 --> 01:10:18,673
of being hit so hard with a curtain rod
that the welts bled,

1382
01:10:18,714 --> 01:10:20,579
of being half starved to death

1383
01:10:20,616 --> 01:10:23,244
because they forgot to say grace
at the table.

1384
01:10:23,285 --> 01:10:24,877
- You're wrong, Father.

1385
01:10:24,920 --> 01:10:26,854
My mother was a good person.

1386
01:10:26,889 --> 01:10:31,326
- You've made her a good person
in your own mind, son.

1387
01:10:31,360 --> 01:10:34,329
She was a monstrous person.

1388
01:10:34,363 --> 01:10:36,831
I knew her.

1389
01:10:36,865 --> 01:10:39,993
And some monstrous part of her
is still in that house.

1390
01:10:40,035 --> 01:10:41,662
I would've told you earlier,

1391
01:10:41,704 --> 01:10:45,231
but everybody was so afraid
of telling you things

1392
01:10:45,274 --> 01:10:46,536
that you didn't remember.

1393
01:10:46,575 --> 01:10:49,567
[table rattling]

1394
01:10:54,883 --> 01:10:55,975
- Tell me something, Father.

1395
01:10:56,018 --> 01:10:58,009
These alleged abuses you talk of,

1396
