did you witness them firsthand
for yourself?

1397
01:11:00,823 --> 01:11:03,121
- No, they were relayed to me
by your Aunt Marlene.

1398
01:11:03,158 --> 01:11:06,286
- Then it's hearsay,

1399
01:11:06,328 --> 01:11:09,491
testimony of conduct
not directly observed.

1400
01:11:09,531 --> 01:11:12,830
It's hearsay.

1401
01:11:18,540 --> 01:11:20,531
- No, you know what's rude?

1402
01:11:20,576 --> 01:11:22,771
A child having a liver lacerated

1403
01:11:22,811 --> 01:11:24,870
by a doctor who's hopped up
on pain pills.

1404
01:11:24,913 --> 01:11:25,902
That's what's rude.

1405
01:11:25,948 --> 01:11:27,176
- That's not fair.

1406
01:11:27,216 --> 01:11:28,274
- Kid comes under your care.

1407
01:11:28,317 --> 01:11:29,648
You know this guy's history.

1408
01:11:29,685 --> 01:11:33,712
Have a conversation about how he
appeared that morning.

1409
01:11:33,756 --> 01:11:36,657
- No, Jennifer Burkhardt had
a conversation with Dr. March, not me.

1410
01:11:36,692 --> 01:11:38,319
- I don't care who it was.

1411
01:11:38,360 --> 01:11:39,622
You were aware that he...

1412
01:11:43,032 --> 01:11:44,624
- [screaming]

1413
01:11:44,667 --> 01:11:48,068
No, no!

1414
01:11:48,103 --> 01:11:49,695
No, no!

1415
01:11:49,738 --> 01:11:51,797
[gavel bangs]

1416
01:11:51,840 --> 01:11:54,502
- You gonna object to any of this?

1417
01:12:03,185 --> 01:12:04,243
- That's courthouse gossip.

1418
01:12:04,286 --> 01:12:06,083
- It's not.

1419
01:12:06,121 --> 01:12:08,180
- Hey, partner.

1420
01:12:08,223 --> 01:12:09,622
How you doin', buddy?

1421
01:12:09,658 --> 01:12:13,958
Listen, um, I was wonderin' if
we can have a moment alone.

1422
01:12:15,597 --> 01:12:17,292
Hey.

1423
01:12:17,333 --> 01:12:19,301
Riley said you're actin'
all funky in court.

1424
01:12:19,335 --> 01:12:20,768
What the hell is goin' on
with you, huh?

1425
01:12:20,803 --> 01:12:21,792
Huh?

1426
01:12:21,837 --> 01:12:22,826
And don't say "nothin'."

1427
01:12:22,871 --> 01:12:24,065
And don't say, "It's personal,"

1428
01:12:24,106 --> 01:12:26,233
"We don't go there,"
'cause today we're gonna go there.

1429
01:12:26,275 --> 01:12:27,572
- You want to go there today, Sully?

1430
01:12:27,609 --> 01:12:28,803
Want me to open up?

1431
01:12:28,844 --> 01:12:29,833
Tell you everything?

1432
01:12:29,878 --> 01:12:31,607
- Yes, I do.

1433
01:12:31,647 --> 01:12:33,581
- I've been havin' a little
trouble concentrating

1434
01:12:33,615 --> 01:12:35,640
since I started having these
unsolicited flashbacks

1435
01:12:35,684 --> 01:12:37,549
of being severely abused as a child,

1436
01:12:37,586 --> 01:12:40,248
locked in a closet,
beaten with a curtain rod till I bled.

1437
01:12:40,289 --> 01:12:42,018
- What?

1438
01:12:42,057 --> 01:12:43,046
- And all this on no sleep.

1439
01:12:43,092 --> 01:12:46,619
Shepard gave me some pills for it,
but they've proved to be totally worthless.

1440
01:12:46,662 --> 01:12:49,153
Except when you mix 'em with scotch,
they tend to, you know,

1441
01:12:49,198 --> 01:12:50,563
sort of enhance the scotch.

1442
01:12:50,599 --> 01:12:51,725
But no.

1443
01:12:51,767 --> 01:12:54,463
I can't concentrate on getting dressed,
much less a court case.

1444
01:12:54,503 --> 01:12:56,471
And about the only thing keepin'
me goin' these days

1445
01:12:56,505 --> 01:12:58,564
is a morbid curiosity

1446
01:12:58,607 --> 01:12:59,938
of where exactly it'll be

1447
01:12:59,975 --> 01:13:01,772
that I totally fuckin' lose it.

1448
01:13:04,546 --> 01:13:09,313
So how do you like
our new relationship so far,

1449
01:13:09,351 --> 01:13:10,841
the opening up thing?

1450
01:13:14,123 --> 01:13:15,454
- I like it better.

1451
01:13:22,398 --> 01:13:24,423
- Well, bless your heart, partner.

1452
01:13:24,466 --> 01:13:26,661
I think it rots.

1453
01:13:30,139 --> 01:13:32,073
- Hey.
- Hey, Sully.

1454
01:13:32,107 --> 01:13:33,096
What's happenin'?

1455
01:13:33,142 --> 01:13:34,131
- Where is he?

1456
01:13:34,176 --> 01:13:36,144
- He's in the back, man,
and he looks like shit.

1457
01:13:36,178 --> 01:13:37,167
- Thank you.

1458
01:13:37,212 --> 01:13:38,201
- Want a beer?

1459
01:13:38,247 --> 01:13:40,306
- Yes.

1460
01:13:48,657 --> 01:13:50,852
- I have an idea.

1461
01:13:50,893 --> 01:13:53,088
Why don't we go back
to my office for a nightcap?

1462
01:13:53,128 --> 01:13:54,117
- I have a better idea.

1463
01:13:54,163 --> 01:13:55,994
Why don't you sit down
and spill all the shit

1464
01:13:56,031 --> 01:13:57,760
you've been keeping from me
all these years,

1465
01:13:57,800 --> 01:14:00,200
and I won't sue you
for medical malpractice.

1466
01:14:00,235 --> 01:14:02,726
- All right.

1467
01:14:11,547 --> 01:14:12,809
What have I been keeping?

1468
01:14:12,848 --> 01:14:15,646
- That I lived there
and she abused me there.

1469
01:14:15,684 --> 01:14:16,946
- True.

1470
01:14:16,985 --> 01:14:19,419
- And you let me go back
when I didn't know.

1471
01:14:19,455 --> 01:14:20,444
- You knew, Bryan.

1472
01:14:20,489 --> 01:14:21,922
Some part of you knew.

1473
01:14:21,957 --> 01:14:24,926
That's why you went back,
tried to heal yourself.

1474
01:14:24,960 --> 01:14:29,420
- And you're certain of this problem
that needed healing, right?

1475
01:14:29,465 --> 01:14:30,659
- How do you mean?

1476
01:14:30,699 --> 01:14:32,929
- That I lost touch with reality
when she died,

1477
01:14:32,968 --> 01:14:34,435
that I was so young and traumatized

1478
01:14:34,470 --> 01:14:37,098
that I couldn't grasp
that she was really dead.

1479
01:14:37,139 --> 01:14:39,334
So I blocked memories,
hallucinated her.

1480
01:14:39,374 --> 01:14:40,363
- Yes.

1481
01:14:40,409 --> 01:14:41,501
Something like that.

1482
01:14:41,543 --> 01:14:45,240
- And what if I told you
that you are so blind with psychiatry

1483
01:14:45,280 --> 01:14:47,180
that you have totally
missed the boat on this one?

1484
01:14:47,216 --> 01:14:49,184
- Which is?

1485
01:14:49,218 --> 01:14:52,517
- That I am truly being haunted.

1486
01:14:53,922 --> 01:14:55,856
- You don't really believe that.

1487
01:14:55,891 --> 01:14:57,916
I am seeing things
in that house, Doctor,

1488
01:14:57,960 --> 01:15:00,929
and hearing things all the time.

1489
01:15:00,963 --> 01:15:03,488
You think I'm that crazy
all by myself?

1490
01:15:03,532 --> 01:15:05,261
- Yes, I think you're quite ill.

1491
01:15:06,668 --> 01:15:08,829
- You are wrong.

1492
01:15:08,871 --> 01:15:11,169
There's something supernatural
going on in there.

1493
01:15:11,206 --> 01:15:13,538
And I have all kinds of corroboration.

1494
01:15:13,575 --> 01:15:15,133
- Well, let's have it, Oounselor.

1495
01:15:15,177 --> 01:15:16,610
Let's try this thing.

1496
01:15:21,817 --> 01:15:24,047
- My Uncle Ohester, to start with...

1497
01:15:24,086 --> 01:15:26,145
- Your Uncle Ohester was a fool.

1498
01:15:26,188 --> 01:15:27,883
He was superstitious, gullible.

1499
01:15:27,923 --> 01:15:28,912
Did you know

1500
01:15:28,957 --> 01:15:31,084
he reported so many
UFO sightings in the '50s,

1501
01:15:31,126 --> 01:15:33,594
the police wouldn't take
his calls any more.

1502
01:15:33,629 --> 01:15:36,029
- No, I didn't.

1503
01:15:36,064 --> 01:15:38,294
But my aunt was no fool.

1504
01:15:38,333 --> 01:15:39,561
And in the last year of her life...

1505
01:15:39,601 --> 01:15:41,193
- The last year of her life,

1506
01:15:41,236 --> 01:15:44,364
she was suffering
from progressive dementia

1507
01:15:44,406 --> 01:15:47,466
due to advanced
cerebral atherosclerosis.

1508
01:15:47,509 --> 01:15:49,568
I have people who will swear
that she was lucid...

1509
01:15:49,611 --> 01:15:51,238
- She was lucid part of the time.

1510
01:15:51,280 --> 01:15:52,474
That's how it works.

1511
01:15:56,552 --> 01:15:58,042
Father Wymond at Saint...

1512
01:15:58,086 --> 01:15:59,280
- You're gonna quote me a priest?

1513
01:15:59,321 --> 01:16:02,415
They think they're dealing
with the supernatural 9:00 to 5:00.

1514
01:16:02,457 --> 01:16:04,755
You want to stake your sanity on that?

1515
01:16:08,730 --> 01:16:14,691
- Do all kids who are abused
crack up so bad that they see things?

1516
01:16:14,736 --> 01:16:15,930
Or am I just weak?

1517
01:16:15,971 --> 01:16:17,632
- I don't think you're weak, Bryan.

1518
01:16:17,673 --> 01:16:20,506
I think you're carrying more.

1519
01:16:20,542 --> 01:16:22,271
- More.

1520
01:16:23,712 --> 01:16:27,409
- What is the last memory you
have of your mother,

1521
01:16:27,449 --> 01:16:29,440
not including her death?

1522
01:16:31,987 --> 01:16:33,784
- My last memory.

1523
01:16:33,822 --> 01:16:38,020
Hmm.

1524
01:16:38,060 --> 01:16:40,255
She was cooking, I think,
in the kitchen.

1525
01:16:40,295 --> 01:16:43,856
- What was she cooking for?

1526
01:16:43,899 --> 01:16:45,161
- A picnic.

1527
01:16:45,200 --> 01:16:46,258
We were going on a picnic.

1528
01:16:46,301 --> 01:16:47,825
- Yes.

1529
01:16:47,869 --> 01:16:51,464
And what happened with the picnic?

1530
01:16:51,506 --> 01:16:52,905
- Well, I don't remember.

1531
01:16:52,941 --> 01:16:54,932
We wound up not going
for one reason or another.

1532
01:16:54,977 --> 01:16:57,810
- What was the reason?

1533
01:16:57,846 --> 01:16:58,835
- I don't know.

1534
01:16:58,880 --> 01:16:59,869
Maybe it rained.

1535
01:16:59,915 --> 01:17:01,940
- No, it didn't rain, Bryan.

1536
01:17:01,984 --> 01:17:03,451
It was a beautiful, sunny day.

1537
01:17:03,485 --> 01:17:06,886
- Then why didn't we go?

1538
01:17:06,922 --> 01:17:10,016
Because that morning,
when you cleaned your room,

1539
01:17:10,058 --> 01:17:13,027
you left a sock on the floor.

1540
01:17:13,061 --> 01:17:16,394
So instead of going on a picnic,

1541
01:17:16,431 --> 01:17:20,458
you were locked in the closet
for the remainder of the day

1542
01:17:20,502 --> 01:17:23,164
and half the next.

1543
01:17:31,980 --> 01:17:33,004
- A red sock.

1544
01:17:33,048 --> 01:17:34,913
- Yes.

1545
01:17:37,085 --> 01:17:39,280
- I remember.

1546
01:17:39,321 --> 01:17:42,779
Hmm.

1547
01:17:42,824 --> 01:17:44,689
God, how sad is that?

1548
01:17:44,726 --> 01:17:45,750
- Sad?

1549
01:17:45,794 --> 01:17:47,853
It's infuriating, don't you think,

1550
01:17:47,896 --> 01:17:50,922
to be locked in the closet for a sock?

1551
01:17:50,966 --> 01:17:53,799
And you were angry, Bryan, very angry.

1552
01:17:53,835 --> 01:17:57,271
You wanted to lash back.

1553
01:17:57,305 --> 01:18:03,972
So you left some toys
you were playing with

1554
01:18:04,012 --> 01:18:05,843
on the stairs

1555
01:18:05,881 --> 01:18:06,939
near the top.

1556
01:18:06,982 --> 01:18:08,973
- What?
- Some toys.

1557
01:18:09,017 --> 01:18:10,279
A toy truck

1558
01:18:10,318 --> 01:18:14,414
and an antique doll
of your mother's.

1559
01:18:14,456 --> 01:18:16,583
You were five years old.

1560
01:18:16,625 --> 01:18:18,149
She had abused you for five years.

1561
01:18:18,193 --> 01:18:21,685
No one knew about it, no one.

1562
01:18:26,201 --> 01:18:27,190
- Mom, no!

1563
01:18:27,235 --> 01:18:30,033
[retching]

1564
01:18:30,072 --> 01:18:31,664
- Press up against my hand.
- What did I do?

1565
01:18:31,707 --> 01:18:32,696
- Press up.
- What did I do?

1566
01:18:32,741 --> 01:18:33,730
- Easy.

1567
01:18:33,775 --> 01:18:34,764
- What did I do?

1568
01:18:40,282 --> 01:18:42,216
- Any dizziness still?

1569
01:18:42,250 --> 01:18:43,877
- No.

1570
01:18:43,919 --> 01:18:46,217
I had to make a judgment call
in there, Bryan.

1571
01:18:46,254 --> 01:18:47,687
You were in a form of crisis.

1572
01:18:47,723 --> 01:18:49,122
- I'm glad you told me.

1573
01:18:49,157 --> 01:18:50,317
- What are you gonna do right now?

1574
01:18:50,358 --> 01:18:52,019
- I'm gonna go check into
the Gloucester,

1575
01:18:52,060 --> 01:18:54,290
get my stuff
and get out of the house.

1576
01:18:54,329 --> 01:18:56,354
- That's exactly what you should do.

1577
01:18:56,398 --> 01:18:57,626
I'll call you later on.

1578
01:18:57,666 --> 01:18:59,133
We'll set something up
for tomorrow.

1579
01:18:59,167 --> 01:19:00,862
All right?

1580
01:19:00,902 --> 01:19:02,494
- That's what was wrong with her face.

1581
01:19:02,537 --> 01:19:03,731
- What's that?

1582
01:19:03,772 --> 01:19:07,936
- That's what was wrong
with my mother's face.

1583
01:19:10,846 --> 01:19:13,007
She was looking at me.

1584
01:20:08,770 --> 01:20:11,204
[phone ringing]

1585
01:20:11,239 --> 01:20:12,263
This is Bryan Becket.

1586
01:20:12,307 --> 01:20:13,638
Please leave a message.

1587
01:20:13,675 --> 01:20:14,664
Oassie, it's Bryan.

1588
01:20:14,709 --> 01:20:17,974
Pick up.

1589
01:20:18,013 --> 01:20:20,504
What the hell are you still doing in there?

1590
01:20:20,549 --> 01:20:23,882
Didn't you tell me you had to leave?

1591
01:20:23,919 --> 01:20:27,878
Oassie, pick up.

